main event: A UFO sighting of a submarine-shaped object, silver in color, near Washington, D.C. on 14th May 1956, which appeared to remain stationary.
interesting points: The object was described as submarine-shaped and silver in color, unusual for conventional aircraft.
The sighting lasted for one hour, providing a significant duration for observation.
Radar data from the report indicates a round white light silently traversing the sky at a speed of 1200 MPH in about 12 seconds.
Visual observation and radar confirmation of the UFO were reported at Andrews AFB.
The lack of details in the report precluded further evaluation of the sighting.
